</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR135:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR135"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              135-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 135</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 23</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Peace Corps Week. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">April 07, 2026.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 135, Laird.
                          Peace Corps Week.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would proclaim March 1, 2026, to March 7, 2026, inclusive, as Peace Corps Week, in recognition of the 65th anniversary of the establishment of the United States Peace Corps, as provided. The measure would also support awarding Peace Corps volunteers a Congressional Gold Medal to honor their distinguished service to the United States.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_8A23ADF1-C915-4329-97DA-F7A47C19F6DB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The United States Peace Corps, established by President John F. Kennedy on March 1, 1961, by signing Executive Order No. 10924, is celebrating its 65th anniversary in 2026 in recognition of nearly 240,000 Peace Corps volunteers who have served our nation in more than 140 host countries since the program began; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_43DF244C-6E7A-42ED-A3CB-7AD7667935C0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Peace Corps has become an enduring symbol of our nation’s commitment to promoting international peace, encouraging progress, creating opportunity, and expanding development at the grassroots level in the developing world; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_2EF15E90-2396-4315-A75D-3D07F5DF5360"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Peace Corps volunteers have made significant and lasting contributions in agriculture, business development, information technology, education, health, and environmental preservation, and have improved the lives of individuals and communities around the globe; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_7E9658CE-6294-4503-9FD2-4C7533049365"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The State of California has contributed 32,503 Peace Corps volunteers, the most of any state, including 329 in 2025; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_382FD60A-469B-403C-AE1F-48CDBB6258CF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, A substantial number of returned Peace Corps volunteers have served as members or staff of the Legislature; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_385CA541-0AAC-4294-95E7-2F8E9E5DF54D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Returned Peace Corps volunteers throughout California continue to volunteer on behalf of low-income, underserved Californians; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_453661B0-51FB-48FE-81B0-8C3D4A4289B7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The University of California, Berkeley, ranks first among large colleges and universities for graduates joining the Peace Corps; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_14184F56-790C-4A8E-8D50-4AB6C27FB830"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California has National Peace Corps Association affiliate groups in the Counties of Los Angeles, Orange, San Diego, Santa Barbara, and Ventura and in northern California and the Sacramento Valley; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_827DE252-F3EB-4E23-851C-ADF5D172A1EC"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Legislature recognizes the service of all current and returned Peace Corps volunteers and their work that has helped people all over the world meet their basic needs and promote world peace and friendship, as envisioned by President John F. Kennedy; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E2964779-5BC4-40F0-B342-D005B8C7091B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Peace Corps Volunteers Congressional Gold Medal Act of 2025, introduced as H.R. 5521 on September 19, 2025, and supported by bipartisan cosponsors, is the highest honor that the United States Congress can bestow on a group of civilians for distinguished service to the United States; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_BF99E33F-CA4C-4E92-B477-9C92B41E9ACB"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Awarding a Congressional Gold Medal will recognize the outstanding achievements of Peace Corps volunteers, will educate our nation about the value of Peace Corps service at the 250th anniversary of the signing of the Declaration of Independence, and will serve as a significant opportunity to encourage individuals to join the Peace Corps; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_3A210CBE-3C65-423A-9FF9-0EF902DB01D4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature does hereby proclaim the week of March 1, 2026, to March 7, 2026, inclusive, as Peace Corps Week, in recognition of the 65th anniversary of the establishment of the United States Peace Corps, and acknowledges all current and former Peace Corps volunteers for their outstanding contributions to their host countries and their successful promotion of global peace and friendship; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_FA27F258-7253-4B7C-A32F-B03A551FC0AD"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature does hereby support awarding Peace Corps volunteers a Congressional Gold Medal to honor their distinguished service to the United States; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_31365D8F-A279-4B75-AABB-EDBD99700E74"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
